    "causal_claim": {
      "cause": "habitual function selection without observable outcome change",
      "effect": "stagnation — error signal remains high, reward drops",
      "mechanism": "Hebbian reinforcement of the dominant path crowds out exploration; the bandit over-exploits a locally rewarded action (Agrawal & Goyal, 2012: Thompson sampling requires exploration to avoid local optima)"
